latestPosts.caption:
This is what I wore for this year’s “ Durga Puja Saptami “
I took these pictures almost over a month back from now but couldn’t post them until now. So much happened over the past month that I didn’t have either the will or urge to take the time out to type a fitting caption, add the relevant hashtags, mention all the details and then upload these pictures. Whatever happened or is still happening was very overwhelming for me both physically and emotionally and I will share everything with you when the time is right. For now just know that I love delivering content for you guys. I love creating and sharing different looks for you. Trust me when I say this, the growth that I have seen in much less than a year, the work that I got in this very short time is all because of your love and support and I by no means take that for granted. I love you all and without you I couldn’t be anything that I am now or that I wish to be in the future.
Keep loving. Keep Supporting. And Keep Believing. Love and hugs 🤗❤️
